Yesterday hundreds of students and workers from various universities protested in the CT CBD. CAPE TOWN - The City of Cape Town says six protesters were arrested during violent clashes with police yesterday. On Wednesday, hundreds of students and workers from various universities protested in front of Parliament during Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan's medium-term budget speech.Police used stun grenades and rubber bullets to disperse protesters, who in turn pelted them with rocks and glass bottles.The City's JP Smith says several law enforcement vehicles, Golden Arrow buses and buildings were damaged during the protest in the Parliament precinct.&quot;A total of six arrests were made, four for public violence and two for the assault of an officer. We are calling on affected residents and businesses to please open cases with SAPS as the video footage of the event is available and will be used to prosecute offenders.&quot;(Edited by Shimoney Regter)